Arena Breakout is a tactical shooter with realistic graphics. It is one of the few mobile games that features truly hardcore gameplay. Here, you need to think through every step, stay aware of your surroundings, and listen carefully for nearby gunshots or footsteps, because if you get killed, you will lose everything. The gameplay is close to Escape from Tarkov; you are dropped in a random location on the map, and to win, you must make it to the extraction point alive. Of course, you won't be alone on the map—other players will try to kill you and take everything in your bags. So, you need to move stealthily: hide behind cars, crawl through grass, and avoid drawing unnecessary attention. When you kill someone or find a supply crate, you have to search it to see what's inside. This is done by clicking on the magnifying glass icon and waiting a few seconds, all while staying in the inventory screen, and only then will you see what items can be taken. To avoid being killed with a single shot while looting, you'll need good body armor and a helmet. These can be purchased from agents or at the auction, but gear will cost you a lot of Koens. If you don't have enough in-game currency, we offer you to buy Arena Breakout Bonds and exchange them for Koens. With them, you can acquire top-tier gear and weapons, as well as medkits, bandages, and armor-piercing bullets. With a powerful shotgun, you can shoot enemies at close range, and good armor will protect you from bullets. Alternatively, you can buy a sniper rifle and hunt for enemy heads without exposing yourself to danger.

In Arena Breakout, you will be fighting from a first-person perspective, which means you'll constantly see your gloved hands and chosen weapon in front of you. When you get tired of looking at bland, gray-shaded guns, you can buy Arena Breakout Bonds and spend them on skins for your weapons, knives, and gloves. If you're playing as part of a team, it would also be wise to use a unique outfit for your gear so your teammates don’t mistake you for an enemy and accidentally shoot you.

All transactions on FunPay are monitored by a security system that holds the funds in reserve until you receive your item. Once payment is made, the seller gets a notification and is obligated to fulfill your order. After you confirm that the bonds are on your account, don’t forget to click the “Confirm Order Completion” button; this will automatically release the funds to the seller.

How to buy Arena Breakout Bonds

  1. Choose an offer.
  2. Contact the seller.
  3. Pay for the order.
  4. Receive the Bonds.
  5. Confirm order completion.

For Sellers

Some players spend money on top-tier weapons and gear, while others enjoy vibrant skins and are willing to shell out cash to customize their equipment. In both cases, they need premium currency, so selling Arena Breakout Bonds will be easy. If you want to help players with in-game purchases and make money off the price differences, we invite you to become a seller on our marketplace.
